==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} [[disgisen]], [[disguisen]], borrowed from {{etyl|fro}} [[desguiser]] (modern [[déguiser]]), derived from [[des-]] "[[dis-]]", from {{etyl|la}} [[dis-]], and [[guise]] "guise", from a Germanic source.

===Pronunciation===
* ''General American'' {{IPA|/dɪˈskaɪz/}} {{SAMPA|/dI"skaIz/}}
* {{hyphenation|dis|guise}}
* {{rhymes|aɪz}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# [[attire]] (e.g. [[Clothing]]) used to [[hide]] one's identity or assume another.
# {{figurative}} The appearance of something on the outside which masks what's beneath.

